column16: As you enter the building there is a strong musty/mildew smell. I automatically took my medication, but the showroom was much better. I was able to stay and enjoy the show.  I realize the building is old and there isn’t much that you can do, but you might get it checked.

column15: Charming theater, friendly staff. Not a bad seat in the house.  The sound quality was stellar (I often struggle to hear), as was the general ambiance, lighting, etc. Easy access to nice, clean restrooms. The availability of drinks/bar was a nice touch. Advance “what to know”info was high quality and timely. Great experience. Very much enjoyed the more intimate setting. We will be back.
Terrific!  Love her shows!  Good sound, good lighting, good value!
Very fun- neat venue!

We absolutely loved Paula Poundstone!!  She is a fabulous entertainer!!  Her show was sold out last time she was in Walla Walla so we were thrilled to catch her this time.  We would definitely go see her again given the chance.  The quality, lighting, sound, and value were all great.
column16: In the future, an intermission or at least a 5 minute chance to stand and stretch our legs would be much appreciated.  My legs were uncomfortably numb after an hour and a half into the show.

column15: The lighting was fine. We were up in the southside balcony and had a tremendous difficulty hearing her whole dialogue. I do not think the balcony has any speakers aimed at the seats, so I was straining to hear her - particularly the punch lines. Perhaps this is something that should be addressed. Two hours of solid standup! Other than the fact we only could hear a part of the dialogue, she was wonderful.
Paula was excellent, as is the seating. However the sound was somewhat distorted at times (I do have hearing aids so could hear well but some words were muddled)
All good.
column16: Speaker interacted with audience. However I could not discern what the college student said as her voice was very soft. It would have been better if Paula repeated what she said over the microphone.
